AWS RDS Proxy
-------------
Amazon RDS proxy is fully managed, high available database proxy for Relational database Service. Using the RDS Proxy makes the applications highly scalable, more resilient to the database failures.
	
The Server-Side applications build on modern technologies (like microservices platform built and deployed on containerized cluster environment) or Serverless technologies can have large number of open connections to the database servers. These applications may open and close database connections at an high-rate, that exhast the database memory and computing resources.
	
Amazon RDS Proxy allows us to have an shared connection pool to the database, that improves the database efficiency and application scalability. Rather than the applications maintaining an connection pool to the underlying database, the RDS proxy creates an distributed/shared connection pool and distributes the connections to the applications when requested.
